*******************************************************************************
********                   DR SCHULZ'S NAVY SIMULATOR                   *******
*******************************************************************************

This program was designed to be the supporting graphics engine for the Navy
Simulation project in CSC-231. In order to configure what features you would
like to use, toggle the options (between 0 or 1) in the CONFIG.txt file.

Using this engine requires certain convetions in order to properly interface.
They are as follows:

1. All student files should be copied into the usr/ directory in order to be
 included and compiled (this may differ on Microsoft machines).

2. Class Names

3. Function Names
